[32m+[m[32m# Railway Setup Checklist[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Step 1: Get Railway Token[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Go to [Railway.app](https://railway.app)[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Sign up / log in[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Go to Settings → API Keys → Create API Token[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Copy the token[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Step 2: Add GitHub Secrets[m
[32m+[m[32mGo to your GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → New repository secret[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mAdd these **required** secrets:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Secret Name | Value | Example |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| `RAILWAY_TOKEN` | Your Railway API token from Step 1 | `rly_...` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `RAILWAY_PROJECT_NAME` | Unique project name | `haloit-backend` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT` | Your Azure OpenAI endpoint | `https://willemhattingh-8180-resource.openai.azure.com/` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `AZURE_OPENAI_API_KEY` | Your Azure OpenAI API key | `xxxxxxxxxxxxx...` |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m### Optional secrets:[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m| Secret Name | Value | Example |[m
[32m+[m[32m|---|---|---|[m
[32m+[m[32m| `SUPER_ADMIN_OWNER_EMAIL` | Owner email | `willem.hattingh@haloitservices365.co.za` |[m
[32m+[m[32m| `JWT_SECRET` | Custom JWT secret (auto-generated if not provided) | `your-secret-here` |[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Note:** The Azure deployment name (`DeepSeek-V4-Pro`) is already configured in the workflow.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Step 3: Push to main[m
[32m+[m[32mOnce secrets are added, push any commit to `main`:[m
[32m+[m[32m```bash[m
[32m+[m[32mgit add .[m
[32m+[m[32mgit commit -m "Add Railway deployment workflow"[m
[32m+[m[32mgit push[m
[32m+[m[32m```[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Step 4: Monitor Deploy[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Go to GitHub repo → Actions[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Watch the `Deploy Backend to Railway` workflow run[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Once complete, go to Railway web UI to verify your app is running[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Troubleshooting[m
[32m+[m[32m- Check GitHub Actions logs: Actions tab → latest run[m
[32m+[m[32m- Check Railway logs: `railway logs` (if you have Railway CLI)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Ensure `RAILWAY_TOKEN` is correct and has deployment permissions[m
